  For projection names containing a backslash, `configure_projections` accepts the name but `attribute_json_path` formats it as `$".<name>"` without escaping; SQLite JSON paths do not match keys like `a\b` this way, and `project_one_attribute` treats the failed/missing extraction as an absent attribute. In that scenario the registry says the projection exists, but backfill and future writes never populate `canonical_attributes` or `property_search_index` for that attribute.

- [P2] Update the Rust public interface contract — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15d/src/rust/crates/fathomdb/src/lib.rs:46-47
  These new `Projection*` re-exports make the projection registry types part of the public Rust facade, but only the Python and TypeScript interface docs were updated; `dev/interfaces/rust.md` still lists the old governed type set and public surface. The repo invariant requires public Rust API changes to update the interface doc in the same PR, otherwise the Rust contract is stale immediately after this change.
